50|$|The {{dress of}} <b>the</b> <b>Armenians</b> {{reflects}} a rich cultural tradition. Wool and fur were utilized by <b>the</b> <b>Armenians</b> and later cotton that was {{grown in the}} fertile valleys. Silk imported from China was used by royalty, during the Urartian period. Later <b>the</b> <b>Armenians</b> cultivated silkworms and produced their own silk.|$|R
