5|$|In May 2016, {{during his}} visit to Yerevan, FIDE President Kirsan Ilyumzhinov said that, after talking to <b>the</b> <b>Armenian</b> Chess Federation {{chairman}} Serzh Sargsyan (also President of Armenia), he heard no refusal about their participation. The vice-president of <b>the</b> <b>Armenian</b> Chess Federation Smbat Lputian responded that Armenia was still discussing the matter and had not decided on the matter yet. In July 2016, Lputian announced that (based upon discussion within the federation) <b>the</b> <b>Armenian</b> chess team would not participate in the Chess Olympiad.|$|E
